# Shared agent instructions

Do **not** duplicate full policy here. Read `.agents/instructions/` before non-trivial work:

1. `.agents/instructions/karpathy-guidelines.md` — coding behavior
2. `.agents/instructions/project-guidelines.md` — language, git, deploy, stack
3. `.agents/instructions/agent-tooling-guardrails.md` — MCP-first browser; no silent Playwright
4. `.agents/instructions/session-handoff.md` — when updating `docs/SESSION_HANDOFF.md`
5. `.agents/instructions/lane-based-development.md` — when using lanes (optional)

When **resuming**, read `docs/SESSION_HANDOFF.md` first.

## Quick rules

- Respond in **Traditional Chinese (繁體中文)** unless the user asks for another language (customize in project-guidelines).
- Read `docs/CURRENT_STATUS.md` and roadmap docs before large changes.
- Do not add Playwright or similar to `package.json` without explicit user approval.
- For Zeabur ops: load Zeabur skills when configured in project-guidelines.

See `.agents/README.md` if present.
